1. ## Objective  {#objective}

   

The objective of this document is to outline the different approaches for setting up and testing Codidact on a local environment using Docker and Playwright.

* Approach : The approach involves setting up Codidact on localhost using Docker and executing test cases with Playwright in JavaScript.

* Chosen Approach : Approach (I’ve chosen this approach because installing codidact through docker is a lot easier and efficient and I’ve chosen Playwright to write test cases because Playwright is faster than selenium and it’s support multiple browsers without using separate web browsers and it is easier to setup and it's also have better features than selenium )

2. ###   Description {#description}

            Codidact is installed and runs locally on port 3000 using Docker. The following  
            Steps were followed:                                              

* Installed and configured Docker to set up Codidact.  
* Used Docker Compose to run the necessary containers.  
* Configured Letter Opener Web to activate the sign-in ID for user authentication.  
* Ensured that Codidact was successfully running on localhost:3000.  
* Implemented Playwright in Visual Studio Code to automate and test various functionalities using JavaScript.

                          Pros:

* Easy to set up and configure using Docker.  
* Automated testing using Playwright enhances efficiency.  
* Letter Opener Web simplifies email activation for testing.  
* Localhost environment ensures a safe and controlled testing space.

                          Cons: 

* Requires a good amount of system resources (RAM and processing power).  
* Initial setup might be complex for beginners unfamiliar with Docker.

  3. ###   Pre-requisites  {#pre-requisites}

     1. ### Hardware Requirements  {#hardware-requirements}

* Minimum 8GB RAM  
* Multi-core processor (Intel i5 or equivalent)  
* SSD storage preferred for faster performance

     

  2. ### Software Requirements  {#software-requirements}

* Docker and Docker Compose  
* Node.js and npm  
* Playwright framework  
* Visual Studio Code (VS Code)  
* Letter Opener Web for email activation

  3. ### Networking Requirements   {#networking-requirements}

* Internet access to download dependencies  
* Localhost network setup to access Codidact at localhost:3000  
* Proper firewall configuration to allow Docker container communication
